  "body": "/kind feature\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nI ran this command on top of a directory that had an invalid yaml\r\n\r\n`kubectl apply --validate=true --dry-run=true --filename=dir_with_multiple_yamls`\r\n\r\nkubectl reported this error:\r\n\r\n`error: error converting YAML to JSON: yaml: line 17: could not find expected ':'`\r\n\r\nFrom that error message, one has no idea which file contains the syntax error.\r\n\r\nNote that on certain different errors, filename is being reported, i.e. when you create a file that just contains \"--\".\r\n\r\n**Minimal example**:\r\n\r\n```\r\nmkdir /tmp/kubetest\r\ncd /tmp/kubetest\r\necho -e \"--\\na: b\" > broken.yaml\r\nkubectl apply --validate=true --dry-run=true --filename=$PWD\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\non yaml parse error, kubectl should report filename as well as the line number -- at least in case directory is specified in kubectl apply\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): v1.7.3+coreos.0 & v1.9.3+coreos.0\r\n",
